Description: Egypt, view of ruined temple complex at Karnak. Obelisk at left. Small group of adult males walking at centre, one wearing military uniform, others wearing gowns, caps. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: This part of ruins known as hypostyle hall. J M Hudson, 27/01/1998. Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
